No, I can't remember the funeral except that he was buried in the - Colchester cemetery. And my father, being a stonemason, he carved the stone. When he came to visit us some many yea
rs later we were living then across the way there in Graces Walk and his object of coming to stay with us was to try and find - the boy's grave. And he spent the best part of two to three weeks backwards and forwards to Colchester and he never did find it
 and no one can find any record of it. Maybe the cemetery's no longer there or it's been built on and - I know he was so upset about it that he - he spent a lot of time trying to find it.
