\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, because - my people - were a little different to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 lots}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 parents. My father was a most independent kind of man and he never mixed much with relatives once he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
. He used to do that - because he said it prevented family quarrels you see. So - and when we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 - he said to me - now - you've taken on a new life, he said, you're master of your own ship - he said - all the best of happiness to you. He said, mo
ther and I will not bother you. We will come and see you when you ask us to come. And when he came, he came over there several times, at the end of about ten days he'd say, son, he said, I think - I'd better go home, he said, because we don't want to outs
t
ay our welcome and, he said, we've enjoyed ourselves, he said, but you can stay too long. And he used to go. And then he wouldn't come again until we asked him to come, he wouldn't - they wouldn't butt in on us. He wouldn't come in on us you know like som
e parents do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 That's rather unusual don't you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, but - he never did - interfere with us. No.
