Oh that was the Irish one. I could use an expression but - as a boy I remember it too well. She had - she was comfortable off. And she sent me one day to the shops round the corner which was a fruit
 shop, and when she bought things she bought them in biggish quantities, and she asked me to bring back a small - they used to have baskets about that high and about that round - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 
strawberries}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 . When I got back, I can remember it as plain as anything, she lo
oked at these strawberries and looked at me. She said, you're a most naughty boy. I - looked - I remember saying to her, why? She said, you've eaten some of those. Now she could well afford to forget all about that. I hadn't touched one and it annoyed me 
