\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 Now coming down the next one, the next man was a stoutish chap that played amateur football for - a northern professional club and he used to be the sports master. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Now he was an awfully nice man. Knew how to handle boys, handle - things generally. He hardly ever used the cane, he used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 use}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  words instead. And he used to take us out training for football. Well, I', sorry to say, but he also committed suicide.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Which was the one that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  to the headmistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Now the one - there wasn't one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  to the headmistress - there was one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  to a mistress. Yes. One of the girls. Now th
at was Mr Chandler. Well now he was a - a quiet individual and - he didn't say much to the boys but when he did he meant what he said and they know that and they obeyed him and he seldom used the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 He achieved discipline through other means?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Yes. Then we had another one, a Mr Routledge. He was another different type of man. He used to use not only the cane but his hand. And by gosh he used to dish it out with his hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 On the ears and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. And many a time there'
s been parents up complaining about it. In fact, one boy - ran home and brought back his sailor brother. Well now - that man - didn't die a natural death. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did he take his own life too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 That's four then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Five altogether. And 
- the headmaster himself - a Mr Brinicombe, was a tall elegant looking man, always in a frock coat and top hat. Always. Nice - very well dressed, very very smartly dressed, good looking man with a nice dark - little small mustache. Now he had a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 habit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  - whe
n you had - in trouble, you had to go and get what was known as the punishment book. And you had to get it off of him in his office. Now not only did he allow the teacher to give you two strokes but if you'd been really bad he used to give you two himself
 
and when he did he used to put his - bite his tongue you know, really - really - cross. Well now, some many years later, he committed suicide. I think that was four or five there. Yes. Whether it was the - teaching they did or - I just don't know - just o
ne of those things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did your parents ever come up and complain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. No. Because I - well, I never was in that position, I - I can only remember being - lightly caned once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Even the one who was really }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 vicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  with the cane, he didn't go for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
No, 'cos I happened to be in his class two - the last two years, and I did hardly any study at all because - I say I was - I was pretty brilliant - pretty brilliant as a school - as a boy at school and I became more or less his office boy - the 
headmaster's office boy for the last year anyway, until I got the job. Then a friend of my father's introduced me into the - Pearl Insurance Company, which was then on Adelaide House on London Bridge, and - I started work there. Having a knowledge of shor
thand and - typewriting and everything else. Which was the thing for boys in those days, they used to go into offices you see, it was a clean job and a pensionable job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were there women shorthand typists?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, not in those days. They came when the - when the first war broke out. When we came back}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10686276\charrsid15798853  after}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  the war the place - the offices were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10686276\charrsid15798853 full}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  of women. And they were known then, they suddenly became instead of - typists they became secretaries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What had your title been when you started, what were you called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh office boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Though you did shorthand and typing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You were called an office boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Used to do all the sticking down of the envelopes and - all the - filing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you run messages too or was that a different job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, that's a different job. A uniformed man had that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 How did you feel about this first job, were you interested in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, I got up quite well on - the time the war came along I was called up, being in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 Territorial}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 already you see, and - I'm a life member of the - my old unit and - when the war broke out - they - a knock on the door at - about one o'clock in the morning - and - my father went down and a policeman. First thing my father thought, oh, what have I
 been up to because I'd been to Brighton with the - the lads you see. Teenage lads. And - 'cos we used to go down to Brighton for two - for a shilling and two bob you know. And - my father said to him - what - what - can I help you - what - what do you wa
n
t? So he said, well, he said, I - I want Gunner Chambers. Well my father said, he's only just come in - he's been away for the - you know - all day, he's only just come in. Can I take it? So the policeman said, no, I must give it to him personally. Of cou
r
se I had to get out of bed, come down and - he gave me this call-up summons you see, to report immediately at the - at the headquarters, which was then in Loughborough Junction. And - I said to father, I'm not going, I'm going to have some sleep first. So
 
I went back to bed and I went up to the office, got up there about ten, low and behold as I explained the other day, most of the - these big companies encouraged the Territorial efforts and as a result was when I got up there all - ninety percent nearly o
f the offices - desks and that were all vacant. They'd all been called-up you know like I had. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 
So of course we had to straighten ourselves out and pack our things up and for those who weren't called up or weren't in Territorial, we had to just hand over and leave them there and come and report. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 And I never went back again until 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You were away all that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes. Oh yes. I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 demobbed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 , as they call it, at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853  Wimbledon,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 the first batch at Wimbledon, Wimbledon Common. And from there I went back to work. Having a decent job and that they were prepared to take me back right away. I didn't have to wait like some chaps you see. So I went back to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 So when you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 in 1918 were you just given tie off to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, that was during the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 So they let you have leave for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, they give you - well, I got a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 But you were really away from home all those years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Thinking back on your schooldays, do you remember your parents ever going up to the school of a meeting of any kind with the teachers?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. None whatever. They didn't have those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did they take an interest in your schoolwork or did they just leave you to get on with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh, they - yes, they used t
o interest themselves in it, knowing that I was fairly good at school you see. Matter of fact, I was much better than my sisters and - one of my sisters, well how - how she got on I just wouldn't know but she wasn't very brilliant. The other one wasn't ba
d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you went to school in West Norwood how did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Walk. We all walked in those days, they had no school buses and - if you had a bicycle you were - your parents were considered very rich.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you come home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. We were about - five to ten minutes from school, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Can you remember if, at that school, there were any children left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What do you mean left out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Who didn't make friends, who were always on the edge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well you used to get - one here and there but not many, they used to quite a - quite a jolly little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 bunch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  of children as far as I remember as a child myself you see, up to the age of fourteen you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Thinking of the children who were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  out of things, can you remember anything about them, why do you think that they were left out in the cold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well of course in those days - money was - a great problem and unemployment }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 stepping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  in meant that money was a bigger problem. And a
 lot of cases, a lot of children were out of things because their parents hadn't got the money, not even a few coppers, to allow their children to take part in lots of these things at school. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 In fact, so much so that some of them couldn't - hadn't even boots to wear to come to school. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
And that put them out - they were back - all backward all the time you see. Especially in some of the London schools, they were shocking.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Those particular children whose parents were very poor and found it difficult to manage, did they look different, could you pick }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 them out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  just to look at them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 As a child looking at another child I mean - weren't aware of it you see, not at that age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you have any children that came from the work house or example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. No, the poor law people were mostly elderly people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 There weren't children there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
No. No. No. They were known as alms houses you see and - that was one of the things as you got on - grew up, you found that people were refusing aid because they
 were afraid it might be known as the poor law you see. And they were a bit independent some of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you know if the teachers gave some children more favourable treatment than others
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, yes, if they'd got - one who was a little bit bright, he used to get a quite a little bit of treatment different. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 As a matter of fact I did - I being as I say, tip boy and - and - fairly good I mean I used to get little chances of doing things that they didn't you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 The master used to snatch a few - quarter of an hour or something and - if he could get me he'd teach me something else you see. Because I could pick it up perhaps a bit quicker than some of the others you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you know whether any of the teachers would favour a child because it came from a better off home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Oh no, no, no, they didn't do that, no, no. If - there were a god many children - well I say children, I was one myself, but - remembering that - some of the children were perhaps a little bet less fortunate than I was
 as regards home life. They probably - missed a lot at school. Because they - they've - they were in a sort of little category where they took longer to learn than other - some of the others. And I should think now, taking the - the schools today for inst
ance, I should think that a teacher finds it most difficult sometimes of - with children, because they're not all brilliant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 But as far as favouring children because their parents were well off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, that didn't happen, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were there children in the school whose parents were really quite well off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were there children of fairly well-to-do business people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. You see, in these areas in London - you got - say, our school was there about ten minutes away ther
e was another postal area. Now those people all had cap and apron servants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Quite nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Yes. Up here you found another branch, they were similar. Then out here you'd find perhaps a poorer - only just half a bus ride away. Well those children came from all those places, all those places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 So people who kept servants, their children attended your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 They could attend our school, yes, And did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Their parents didn't send them to another school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, not unless they qualified from this school by means of scholarships when they could afford to send them to a better school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Would you say you had a pretty wide social mixture at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 My sister -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You were saying how you used to get to Brixton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Horse drawn tram. They used to change the horses half way at a pub called the George Canning which is half way between West Norwood and Brixton. Well then - Brixton was a market place as you probably know. And we used to go there 
Saturday evenings used to be - oh let's go to Brixton. Well now down there you had the theatre and the music hall. The theatre was known as the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 Brixton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  Theatre and the music hall was known as the Empress Music Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 And you used to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well, yes, occasionally on the Saturday night. I personally used to go to the theatre 'cos I'm not keen on - variety stuff. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 And we used to watch all these - very old plays written by Albert Melville which were all - dealing with baddies you know, one of them called the Bad Girl of the Family. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 That type.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did she turn out good in the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well, she was a good person in the end but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 They usually had a moral didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, they did, they - used to have a different one each week you se
e. And - that was our amusement on the Saturday. Used to be football in the afternoon and then theatre or music hall in the evening. Finishing up probably with a - fish - fish and chip supper in the arcade at Sam Isaacs which was a well known - fish shop.
 Then - if you were out shopping and if you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 and you're out shopping you stay in Brixton until eleven or half past eleven at night and you get a joint there for - just - almost a few coppers I was going to say, but - quite as bad as that but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember the names of any of the other plays you saw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Albert Melville, yes, Melville. He used to run the theatre you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 He ran the theatre and wrote the plays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well, no, he didn't write the plays but they used to produce them 
you see. The Melville family who I - were quite a well known family in - in that world at that time, that type of world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did members of the family act in the plays too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 And the play changed every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Change
d every week. I can't think of the others, I know that particular one, the Bad Girl of the Family but my wife might remember some of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you ever go to the music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 I only went perhaps twice, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 It didn't appeal to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
It doesn't now, doesn't - I mean when you've seen one turn you've seen the lot. I mean, I'm not narrow minded or anything like that. But - some of it is real smut I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What about the cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Ah now, the cinema. In West Norwood my parents had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 a shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
. A sweetshop where she - my mother used to make all her own sweets. She had the sweetshop. My father was still at work. When he came home he used to help her make the sweets by pulling the sugar over the hook on the door you see. And we - the
 - in return for the - showing the bills of this - of the - cinema or the movies or whatever you like to call them - they used to issue so many free tickets which I used to go with on the Saturday afternoon and in return for that we use to get in for a pe
n
ny. And that used to be in - in Brixton. Now I used to go every week and there was a serial, In Acre Lane Brixton, opposite the town hall, and there was series they were running, a pirate series and of course being - a boy like other boys, there was alway
s a rush and we all wanted to see this series and we - we didn't want to miss any, we had to see the lot to get the story. Well that used to be penny on the tram to Brixton, go to the pictures and back again and do the whole lot for about tuppence. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Can you remember what age you would have been when you first went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh I'd be what - about - ten probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Shortly after you came to West Norwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, yes, shortly after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Your mother opened that sweetshop shortly after you came to West Norwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Oh yes. In the High Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Was it separate from the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh - yes. We lived at - the back of the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Was it open ordinary shop hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 That was quite long hours in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Yes. Oh there was no limit you see. You could go and buy a packet of cigarettes at - what - ten o'clock if the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13189204\charrsid15798853 tobacconist}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  was open. There was no shutting at eight o'clock, and then eventually they bought in shutting at eight o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did she serve in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Anybody help her at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Father used to help her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What sort of difference did that sweetshop make to the family income?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well not a great deal but it used to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Was it all home made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Everything was homemade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you have any duties in the shop to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 It was just your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Can you remember whether many people came in and bought the things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, used to be quite a number of people come in. She used to get - occasional orders for - decorations,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853  sweet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  decorations, like her mother used to do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 She'd helped her mother with that of course and learnt the trade from her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Neither would pass it down you see to anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you went to the theatre, did you do that before you left school or was that afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, that was after school - after I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  school. No I wasn't allowed out to any of those things, not - not as a schoolboy. No. I believe I told you the other week, I didn't get a door key until I was twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 After you left school you were allowed to go to those things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes. I'd be about fifteen or sixteen when I started to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you go on your own or with a group or with one friend?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well - two boys, but then my father used to pick out the particular things I had to go and see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 He kept an eye on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. 'Cos I - until I was about - seventeen and I joined the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 Territorials}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  seventeen or eighteen and - then I - I began to go out a bit more then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 But up 'til then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
The only restrictions put on me then was if I said I was coming in at a time he expected me in at that time. I didn't have to tell him I was coming in at nine if I didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 intend}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  to come in until eleven. He'd sooner me tell him eleven o'clock and he'd know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did he also keep an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 eye}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  on the sort of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853  company}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  you associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, yes, yes. He used to very often come out and watch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Who you were with you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Unbeknown to me but - my mother used to tell me he used to go out and have a walk and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 If you took a girl out did they like to meet her and know who she was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were you encouraged to bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, encouraged - 
when we got a bit older we - my sisters began to - do the piano and - we used to have a little sing-song now and then but we didn't do a great amount because my father was never keen on that sort of stuff. That's why I had to go out to find it and I went 
to my wife's people who were - very fond of entertaining.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you were a child do you ever remember your parents telling you you shouldn't play with a certain child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, we didn't get that, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You never had any pocket money you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well - I used to get - penny on Saturday morning. Knives forks and spoons on the - on the knife board. I wasn't allowed to go out or do anything until I'd done it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Thinking back to that time before 1918 were you aware of some people belonging to one social class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Oh yes, yes, that was - that was showing then. The people who had the servants used to think they were - the cat's whisker you see. Which didn't always prove to be the case, because there were quite a number of 
people who didn't have maids although they could afford to have maids, they preferred to do their own. But - that went on - the cap and apron went on right until - well, even in Frinton in 194 - 1946 and seven. We were asked out one evening in Frinton and
 the lady she opened the door had got a cap and apron on. As late as that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 In West Norwood would you have put the at the top at that time in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well - they were - better off socially because they could afford the - to pay for the entertai
nment they're going to see or, you know, or have, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What were the other groups or classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well the other groups were people who had much less money and as much as they could do to - to carry on, without going to get help anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were there any people in between or would you divide them into just the two classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, there was - so called middle. That still remains today, the so called middle as they say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What sort of jobs did the men have in that part of London in the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 Well they used to go up to London. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Season ticket holders on the railway you know. Used to go to London Bridge or Victoria.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What about people who kept shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well they were like the normal shops of today. Similar kind of shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Which class would you put them in, with the people who considered themselves the cat's whiskers or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, no, no, some were quite ordinary people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Your mother had a shop didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes. Quite ordinary people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you were a boy were you brought up to call anybody sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. Only people like headmasters or teachers or - not parents and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What about a man that you didn't know, if you spoke to him would your father expect you to call him sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. Not - my father wouldn't. He'd give me the man's name whoever it was and it would be Mr so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you ever have to use the term madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you ever remember being brought up to touch your cap or show respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Yes. Yes. And if you didn't do it you got a rap on the knuckles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Who would you touch your cap to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Ladies and - that knew my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Any lady? It didn't matter what her station in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you have a vicar around and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853  was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 he a person people knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 We didn't see much of the vicar. They're like they are today, they only come when there's some antiques to be bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 He didn't call round and mix much with the people you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, not - not like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were your parents church people or didn't they have anything to do with church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, they didn't go to church, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did they send you to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, Sunday school. Band of Hope, Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Was that church of England or non-conformist?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Church of England. Oh I went to many - I - I went to Baptist church for some time on my own when I was about - in teenage. I went to Congregational when I was in teenage. And - choirboy in the Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You were doing all these things at the same time were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, follow one another, change around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Why did you go to the Baptist church for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well if I could - there was a young lady I knew went. Yes. It used to be a - a well known preacher by the name of Do
ctor Hylie used to be at this church and he was a very fine speaker and a very fine preacher. That coupled with the fact that I knew a young lady there, that enticed me and kept me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 there}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  for a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 And he really was a good preacher was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes. Yes, yes. But he was well known in London. He used to - preach a lot at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 Spurgeon's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  Tabernacle. Oh yes, yes. I also went to Presbyterian too. So I've had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What about the Roman Catholic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, I haven't touched that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 The Presbyterian and Congregational, was there also a young lady there or was that other reasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Presbyterian, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 It was a way of meeting people then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Yes. And then - one was a young lady I knew at a dance who attended the - Church of England one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were you quite a regular attender of these different churches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, not regular but - when I - when I - like I do now, I go when I feel like it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember if your mother or father had anything to do with church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. No. No. No. None whatever, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you know if they had any religious views at all or if they were actually atheists?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, no, they never expressed any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 They didn't talk about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you ever have grace when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Who said that or did the children say it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well - we used to say it - children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember being taught to say prayers or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, as a child, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you belonged to the choir that was Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 That was St Philips church, Cambridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did it have any choir activities like a choir treat or paying the children or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well - payment in those days came to about sixpence I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Sixpence a time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 A week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 And quite a few hours practicing I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Quite a lot. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What about a treat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well most - Sunday schools, or anything to do with church, had what they call a - a treat once a year. Used to go seaside somewhere, or a country place. And you either - there was no cars and you used to go by horse brake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 That would get a lot of children in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Covered brake you see. And - the same thing used to be for men's outings and that all used to be by - this brake. See we hadn't car
s and if you - bicycles were - well - to get a bicycle you've tot to have a shilling or two I mean, you hadn't got that shilling or two you couldn't afford a bicycle and everything was done walking, or going on a tram, penny o a tram or bus - horse bus.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember going on an outing from West Norwood, where did you go to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well we used to go to West }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 Wickham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 , was a country place then, picnicking or - place called Riddlesdown near Purley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you go to Sunday schools of all these different places too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 So you went on quite a number of different treats did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well they didn't have money you know. If you had one a year you were lucky, then - then you only went if your parents could afford the - few coppers whatever it was, or sixpences - to pay for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What age did you discontinue Sunday school altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Ooh I'd be about - when I joined the Territorials, be about seventeen or eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 People went on 'til they were quite old then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes
. Well you see, you went from one, from the Sunday school which was children, up to the next one which was a Bible class and as you got on and - a bit advanced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember what your father's political views were before 1918 if he was active in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Was he an active Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. He used to read a morning paper called the Morning Leader which was the Liberal paper in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you ever remember him expressing political opinions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, he - he - never said much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Have you any idea why he was Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well - the only had - the choice then was between - Liberal and Tory. You had no Labour. No - no Communist, no Labour, only just the two parties in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you know why it was that he was Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well - in those days the Tory, or Conservative as we know it today, were considered to be the snooty people up above with plenty of money. The Liberal were then the second party. In other words, the working man was generally Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 And that's why your father was you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember him ever working for the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. He never did any active -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember him having a poster up or displaying anything in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Only when the voting was on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 He would then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Can you remember what the colours were then for the Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Blue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Would that be yellow for the Conservatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you know if your mother had any views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, she - what father did she did and that's all - she got quite enough to do in the house I think. To worry about politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 At that time many men }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 felt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  that they risked their jobs if they didn't vote the way their employers wanted them to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well that did 
happen. That did happen. I don't know my own father - my own parents case at all but I know that it did happen because as you got older and that and went out to business yourself you read of these things but - they did - they were there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you know if your father was ever under pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. No, I'd - as far as I know, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you actually remember him voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, most conscientious about it too, he'd never miss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember your mother voting in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, she went
 and voted the same way as father did. Each time. She never studied the thing or anything like that. She'd just follow father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you have a vote in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Used to be twenty-one then didn't it? When I first voted, I should - I would be about twe
nty - twenty-one - and I voted Liberal because - I had the same view then as a lot of people did and that is the Conservatives were considered to be the - the moneyed people, people with properties, you see, the ordinary working man had no properties then
,
 it wasn't - they weren't thought of so much in those days as they are today when people own their own properties you see. They were nearly all rented. Therefore we - the people who owned the properties were nearly all Conservatives you see. Of course tha
t's changed today, it's gone the other way round you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you voted did you work for the party at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You just went and crossed your vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember hearing anybody being described as a real lady or a real gentlemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, I've heard people described as either one or the other. That was generally the - a case of where they were - had }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 generous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 , helpful - would assist you in any - you know, if they could. Generally considered by people as being good l
iving people you know. Friendly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Do you remember if there seemed to be a different class or type of person who went to the church of England compared to those who went to the Baptist and the Presbyterian churches?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well I think this existed
 today as it was then, there's still that same - that same attitude. You'll get church people go to church - the vicar will come round and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 he\rquote ll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  talk to you when the service is over, at least they do round her, Old Thomas and one or two others and - you'll get chapel people who come }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 out}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  and they're particularly fond of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 shaking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 hands, chapel people, this may be part of their ritual I wouldn't know. And that's still done today. When - going back a good many years, we always used to think, as young men, at lea
st those that I mixed with a lot, always used to take the church people as being the so called goody-goodies you see and the chapel being the people who - to put it in the Yorkshire phrase, would take all and give nowt. Whether it's like that }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 today}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  I don't
 know but - the different - there's a - there is a difference between church people and chapel people. I'm not saying anything about the - the religious side of it at all, but just the - the personality themselves - the person themselves. I know them here
, I mean, they're just the same today. They're two different - they are different kind of people in their different ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you say good-goodies, what exactly do you mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well - if you went - that's - if you went to church in our - ba
ck in all those years back, and you went to church regularly, morning, noon and night on the Sunday - a lot of these people used to think they were so much better than those who didn't go at all. Now that - used to get me because since I've grown up and b
e
come teenage, middle ate; and bit older still I've come to realize this that - that doesn't follow because in our own personal case here, my mother-in-law was to my mind one of the finest women in - living and yet she didn't go to church much. From a Chri
stian point of view she would give everything and take nothing. She - she didn't go to church, not - on, not once in a blue moon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 She was a Christian in her way of behaving and treating people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Yes. She would help anybody at any time to the 
detriment of herself very often. My wife is - the very image of her too because she's just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Would you say there was any difference in the social class or the money of the two groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well there was a little - distinction between the two
. Few - if there are any functions on and you went to them there was a time when you used to see that - the difference of one moneyed class and the other. You got the people who were ordinary working people who's money was very small, and you got the city
 people who's money was much larger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Which would be more represented at the church or at the chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well the representative part of it was generally the people with money used to give money to the church and - they used to think they were being - you know - that cat's whisker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 The church was the more moneyed group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Than the chapel you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Well chapel, it's coming on a different problem there, chapel people are different, have a different outlook on money to wha
t church people have. Some people give money to the church for the soul object of getting their name in print. I know them here. And - you get another one to the same in the chapel. And yet you'll get another person who'll give something and say nothing. 
No one knows who's given it. Now I suppose you'll - that'll always carry on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were there lots of different standards of living among the people who didn't have so much money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes. Yes, everything was based on - well, your incomes. Well like it is today. Still based on income today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Would you say there was a group in that group of ordinary people who felt themselves superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well - I would say the answer to that is that if you're in the poorer people you're not in a posi
tion to - think you're better off than anybody else, you know jolly well you're not you see. Oh you get the odd ones, yes, well they think they're - well there wasn't so much of that done because there was that big difference between the one and the other
. In those days. You see, we didn't have National Insurance or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Your father was a craftsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you think at that time there was much of a distinction }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 between}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  craftsmen and labourers or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes. Well to learn his trade probably cost - oh in those days anything about thirty pounds was quite a lot of money. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Would you say there was a social distinction in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well there's probably a social distinction as well because a man who can afford
 - his parents can afford thirty pound to put him to an apprenticeship and the other man who's a labourer can't afford that, I mean, obviously there's a - there is a difference and yet - working together they used to mix together and they used to go and h
ave their drink in a pub together. Quite all right, quite friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Would you say that your father had friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well he was not an easy man to make friends you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Was he a reserved type of man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, he - he wasn't easy to make friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did your mother have friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well she was more likely to make friends than father but - I'm afraid father being the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 temperament}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  he was, then mother didn't make the friends she could have made or would have liked to have made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Was that because he didn't encourage entertaining and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
That's right. Yes. I mean she used - in later years she used to go - the women to this sort of - she joined the Co-op or something and they used to have these sort of whist drives
 and she used to go then and he didn't mind because he didn't - he joined in later on and he began to play cards when the war - war finished you see. Things we never had in the house before. So that - they were beginning to turn you see. So in their later
 years before they died they used to - my mother used to go to frequent whist drives. That was her life. Father used to like his book and his pipe and that was it. And - that was their life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Your sister was a lot younger than you wasn't she - twelve years younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Until she was fourteen they hardly went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
No, they didn't go out, they wouldn't leave us you see. That's the one thing that I've got - always have got in their favour is that they never left us. In charge of anybody at
 all, or anybody in charge of us they never did that, they never went out until my youngest sister was fourteen. And then he jolly well told us that they were going and they did and they didn't worry about us then, we used to have to look after ourselves.
 See, not like today - today you get - well. I know cases -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember any occasion when people who weren't relatives came into the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Weren't relatives? Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Friends - or did they not figure in your parents life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 Well they - they - very, very little - very little.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What about neighbours, did a neighbour pop in and sit and chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Not like they do today. No, they used to talk over the fence and that sort of thing
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did your mother ever pop in and have a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, no, no, she - she'd talk over the fence or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 But not in their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did the aunt who lived opposite come in ever and eat with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 seldom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 . Oh, she - she kept herself to - you know - yes. Nothing unfriendly with them but - keep apart you see, just keep apart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Was he much in evidence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well - the bobbies in those days - they were - well I was going to say much more fr
iendly than they are today. They were more or less known to everybody you see. At night time they used to parade, not like they do today, their duties were - they hadn't got torches in those days, they used to have a bulls-eye lantern which used to have a
 bulls-eye - today they've got torches, and panda cars and all that, well they didn't have those. They were - they were quite friendly you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 How do you think they treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well, I say, they were quite friendly, yes. A policeman never treats people badly unless he's interfered with himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Some parents bring their children up and say I'll call a policeman if your naughty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 That's right. That used to be used, well that used to be enough.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did your mother or father say that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, oh yes, many times and that used to be a very good }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 influence.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 The different house you had in Norwood, were they rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, all rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were they all the same landlord or were they different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well - see, in this case probably two landlord - different landlords.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you ever meet him - the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, yes, he was estate agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What were the landlords like, were they good landlords or bad landlords?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Some were good and some were bad,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 In your own particular case, the two landlords in West Norwood, can you tell me anything about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well, they were - he was a - one was an estate agent, used to collect the rents himself and - he wasn't too}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853  bad,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  if you wanted something done, as long as you didn't come the old soldier too much as they say, he would do them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 And the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
The other one, he was not too bad at all. See the houses were probably rented about six - six bob a week, five bob a week you see. Ten bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember when you were a boy and a teenager people using the term rough and respectable at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Rough and ready, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What do you think they meant by it when they used it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well - a rough and ready person is one he has be a 
jolly person, but - and he just takes things as they come. Dress doesn't bother him - he - he's no desire for fashion or anything like that or whatever they like to bring out. He's going to dress as he likes himself and - he's just rough and ready, if peo
ple don't like it well that's just too bad. But he can }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  a very nice and jolly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 persona}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What about rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, rough, when they mean a rough person, is a rough diamond they say don't they. Well, now that's a - that - a chap who's known as a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 rough diamond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 now he - he's one - who - he doesn't mind - doesn't mind anybody, whoever they are - he can face anybody. He's not afraid of anybody, he's just a rough diamond and that's it. He also can be a nice person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What about rough as used as distinct from respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well a respectable person, you take as someone who conducts himself well, never gets into trouble - doesn't interfere with other people and they way, oh he's a nice respectable chap he is. Keeps himself dressed nicely and all that, 
he's respectable. Against which you get other man who's a - a rough man. Well he doesn't bother about either of that. He's not afraid of anybody and he doesn't mind upsetting anybody and - he doesn't mind being upset because he can hold his own and all th
at sort of business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Were you aware of much drinking in West Norwood when you were a boy or a teenager?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
No. Well I suppose one can bring their own life into it. Now - when I became teenaged I joined the Territorials. That was the start, like it i
s for a lot of boys, to have a drink. And - I then used to meet the boys and we used to go from one pub to another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 Pub crawling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well that's what it means you see. And I became then, I used to drink whisky, not much beer, I couldn't stand beer.
 I used to drink whisky and we used to go to a certain pub in West Norwood which is still there today, known as the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 Thurlowe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 Arms and we used to have a hot whisky in a glass nearly as big as that and a thick slice of lemon in it, for sixpence. And that use
d to be our evening session. Well that went on for a long time. Until, as you already know, I lost my first wife, my wife lost her first husband and it was through her that I gave up - going in the pub for a whisky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Through your present wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Ye
s. She said to me - why do you do this, why don't you come home and have a cup of tea or something at home, have a drink at home? And eventually I did. And I became friendly with her brother who is now dead, her sister who lives in Kirby Cross and her sis
t
er's husband, well we all knew each other at schooldays you see and we became friendly and that kept me away from the pub so that today, or for the last ten to twelve - ten or twelve or years I haven't - I've never had a drink - I - I'm not against it but
 I have a bitter lemon you see. I go to Masonic meetings and drink toasts in bitter lemon. But -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Your own father didn't mind you doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, no. The only thing he said to me was when I joined the Territorials and he knew I liked drink that's
 when he said to me, remember this is your home, don't abuse it. And - of course he never came home the worse for drink or anything like that so he didn't expect me to. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 
So I - eventually as a teenager - I met my good lady and - gave up the whisky drinking 
and, I didn't give up drinking entirely but - well - used to drink a little, mostly whisky and - now of course for the last eleven - twelve years I haven't touched any. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
And I haven't smoked, I mean, just the same as smoking, I haven't smoked for ten years now. That's why I tell people it's not difficult to do these things if you can make your mind up to do it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you used to go out and have this whisky was it every evening of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes, oh yes, the usual, it was a ritual. There'd be perhaps seven or eight of us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did your father go to the pub every evening for a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 How often would he go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Generally only Saturdays or - or Sundays when he was home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Do you remember your mother going at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 once}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No. Yet she was born in a pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 In West Norwood did respectable women go to the pub then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, they didn't do - mostly men they used to meet for a chat and talk gardening or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 If you were taking out a young woman would you have a drink together in a pub like they do today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Not - oh no, not like they do today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 It wouldn't be the thing to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, well it - they didn't have the money to do it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 If you'd had the money would it have been an O.K. way of spending the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well, yes, they - they used to go out - yes, they'd do it but they wouldn't spend the money like they do today. You take now, that sixpence for a whisky. Now - people today don't stop at the one. Th
ey might have three or four. Well - where that would cost two shillings then would }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 cost}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 you a pound for today, well you - you just can't - didn't do it. It's just throwing money down the drain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Your first wife, how long was it before she passed away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 What, you mean after we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Less than a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 She had the 'flu didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10686276\charrsid15798853 Died}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  in three days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You'd only been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 that short amount of time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Would you mind telling me where it was you met her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Well that's - same as my wife now, yes, we were all together you see, went to school together. She used to be the pianist for all our little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 singsongs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Your first wife used to be pianist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Yes. She's a good pianist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 How long had you known her before you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh - probably four or five - four years I should think. Because we were at school together you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 did you have any help in having a home, setting up a home, financial help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
No, we hadn't set one up, we were just thinking of doing it when she died. No chance you see. I was still in uniform, I had to go back you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Did you have a wedding with guests and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh - not many, the war was on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 So everything was cut down in that way wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Had she had a job before she got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853  or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes. Yes. Yes, she used to be in one of the local shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Working in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13699159 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
 had she decided to give up work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, well the war was on you-see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 She was going to keep on with her job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Keep on, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 How did you feel about her keeping on, you said your father didn't like the idea of his wife working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, it wasn't the thing done then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 But your wife was going to keep on, how did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well she wasn't - when I came over and - once I was demobbed. It was only while the war was on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 That made such a difference to things didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You didn't mind her working while the war was on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
Oh they had no option, they had to do something you see, they were getting called up you see. My present wife here, she was doing things in this last war. Well you all got called up to a certain age you were called up to do something you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Was she older or younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Can you repeat what you said about the division between craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Well in those days there was always the - the 
so called working class and the so called upper. Of course today the positions reversed. The so called working classes have got plenty of money. The middle class haven't got quite so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 It was different in those days, so you did feel that there was this difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, there was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, I was quite happy in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You had the position of senior clerk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Would you say that when you went to work it changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, not at all, not - not personally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9979616\charrsid15798853 How about enlarging your social contact, or did you not meet any new types of people in your work?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No, well I was always a good mixer with everybody. Have been all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 So it didn't make an alteration in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You were saying in the Territorials people came from all sorts of jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes. That took in everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 When you went out to the pub what were the people there that you mixed with, what sort of jobs did they do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh, varying jobs, from - craftsmen, non-craftsmen, labouring, clerical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966536 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 You were a mixed crowd?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2884641 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9845573\charrsid15798853 Oh yes, yes.
\par }}